[49m[39m  15, 15[0m:[39m[49m **AWS Lambda for feature engineering orchestration.** The feature engineering pipeline (temporal aggregations, derived features, missing value imputation) runs on each prediction request or on a schedule. Lambda handles the stateless, event-driven nature of this work: a new lab result arrives, trigger a feature refresh, score the patient. For patients with ICU stays exceeding 7-10 days, the volume of vital sign data may approach Lambda's 15-minute timeout. In those cases, pre-aggregate vital signs into hourly summaries in a separate pipeline (AWS Glue or SageMaker Processing), or allocate maximum Lambda memory (10 GB) to maximize compute throughput. Include a timeout fallback that serves the most recent successful prediction rather than failing silently.
[0m[49m[39m  16, 16[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Watch out: Lambda timeouts on your sickest patients.** The irony of the timeout problem is that it hits hardest on long-stay ICU patients, who are exactly the ones who most need accurate predictions. A patient on day 14 with continuous monitoring may have 10,000+ vital sign observations. Running temporal aggregations (min, max, mean, std, trend across 4 time windows for 7+ vital signs = 140+ computations on large arrays) on that volume can push Lambda past 15 minutes. The pre-aggregation pattern solves this: run a scheduled Glue job or SageMaker Processing job that rolls up raw vitals into hourly summaries (mean, min, max per hour), stored in a separate DynamoDB table or S3 prefix. The real-time Lambda then reads the pre-aggregated summaries rather than querying the full raw history. This keeps per-prediction Lambda execution under 30 seconds regardless of ICU length of stay. The fallback behavior matters too: if the Lambda does time out, serve the most recent successful prediction (with its timestamp prominently displayed) rather than returning nothing. A 4-hour-old prediction is better than no prediction, as long as the clinician knows it's stale.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  17, 19[0m:[39m[49m **Amazon DynamoDB for prediction storage and serving.**
